  "text": "The MECO spans the interval between 13 and 17 m . At 17 m, directly above the upper boundary of the MECO interval, an 8 m-thick sapropelic interval interrupts the predominantly marly lithology. This interval has a high total organic carbon (TOC) content (up to 3%; Fig. 3 ) and has been subdivided into two subunits, ORG1 and ORG2, separated by a 2 m interval with a normal marly lithology . This study focuses on the interval from 10 to 32 m above the base of the section, within planktic foraminiferal Zones E10-11, E12 and lower E13 [CITATION_1] , corresponding to P12 to lower P14 [CITATION_2] .",
